<TITLE> BNP standing committee sees 12 new faces </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 13 (bdnews24.com)BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia has announced the party's national standing committee, which sees 12 new faces including Tarique Rahman, and will have a term of three years. Khaleda also decided that Khandaker Delwar Hossain will remain in place until a new BNP secretary general is appointed, her press secretary told reporters Sunday night at the BNP chief's Gulshan office. She named the seven joint secretaries general of the executive committee, press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan said. He said Mirza Fakhrul Alamgir was made senior joint secretary general in place of Tarique Rahman. The announcements came five days after the party's fifth national council. The new faces of the 19-member standing committee are Tariqul Islam, ASM Hannan Shah, MK Anwar, Sarowari Rahman, Jamir Uddin Sircar, Mirza Abbas, Goyeshwar Chandra Roy, Abdul Moyeen Khan, Nazrul Islam Khan, Rafiqul Islam Miah, Salauddin Quader Chowdhury. Khaleda's elder son Tarique, being made the party's senior vice-chairman, is also now a member of the standing committee, the party's highest policy-making body. BNP's fifth national councilafter a long hiatus of 16 yearselected Tarique as the senior vice chairman and Khaleda Zia as the unopposed chairperson on Dec 8. bd
